column5: I'm loving this warm weather that we are having right now. I only wish that the water levels would raise in Lake Erie so I can get the boat out there. I don't think I have seen Lake Erie this low In years.
Nice, that's a good sign I have seen a few Bald Eagles in the past 2 weeks out at the Lake and it's nice to see that they are making a come back to the area.
I had a couple of males sguaring off in my yard today.Looking for prime mating space for the season. Spring is sprung,the grass is ris, i wonder where them birdies is

Yea I love this time of year perfect weather for fishing not to hot not to cold and the air is so fresh I have noticed more birds around in the area but I really enjoy seeing the Bald Eagles when I was a kid we only could see them when we were up north but not anymore.
...still a foot of snow on my grass!
I know spring has sprung when you see your fist skunk roadkill.  yup, I passed one today so it's SPRING!
Lol that's a bummer having that much snow still lol. I love the winter but the soft water season is so much more enjoyable for me. I seen a Nice sized deer on the side of the road last night lol.
